content:
Here is the cleaned up text:

Send Messaging Components in Your Customer’s Language
Show any messaging component in your customer’s language with the help of Translation Workbench.

Customize Secure Forms with New Settings
New settings help you customize every step of the form submission experience in Apple Messages for Business. Show a welcome screen before the form questions, and provide a title and subtitle for each form field.

Customize Lists in Messaging Components with New Settings
Try several new settings on the List Selector format to control how messaging components appear in messaging sessions.

Control When Secure Forms Expire in Messaging Sessions
Customize the time limit for customers to submit their responses before the link expires. For example, change it to 60 minutes.

Form Format in Secure Forms Is Generally Available in Messaging for In-App and Web
The Form format is now generally available for Messaging for In-App and Web.

Extend Messaging Components with Custom Constants
Add custom image or text constants to messaging components to control their appearance at a more granular level.

Authentication Messaging Components Improved for Compatibility
Changes have been made to ensure compatibility with Apple Messages for Business REST API.

Auto-Response Components Are Available in Partner Messaging (Beta)
Save agents time by automating common messages to customers using auto-response components in Partner Messaging.

Prevent Unwanted Parameters in Your Auto-Response URL
Configure a corresponding Web Page Parameter in the Messaging Component to prevent unwanted parameters from appearing in your Messaging for Web auto-response URL.
title: Messaging Components Summer '24 Release Notes
